Since 2005, a group of activists have been returning to Moore's Ford Bridge regularly to reconstruct the fateful night in 1946 when two black couples - Roger and Dorothy Malcom and George and Mae Murra Dorsey - were killed by members of the Ku Klux Klan.
No one's ever been convicted of murder.
"It's amazing that not a single person has been arrested in all these years - even though we still see them in our community; even though we know their identities", Tyrone Brooks, who is helping to organize the reenactment, said.
